Usage: addIoRowFiller [-help] -cell {name list} [-fillAnyGap] [-from <coord>]
                      [-ignoreSiteType] [-logic] [-prefix <string>]
                      [-to <coord>] [-useSmallIoHeight] [[-ioRow <rowName> | -powerDomain <string>] [-fillerOrient <R0|R90|R180|R270|MX|MX90|MY|MY90>]]

-help                      # Prints out the command usage
-cell {name list}          # name list of IO filler cell (string, required)
-fillAnyGap                # fill smaller gap by overlapping filler cell
                           # (bool, optional)
-fillerOrient <R0|R90|R180|R270|MX|MX90|MY|MY90>
                           # orientation of new filler instances (string, optional)
-from <coord>              # staring offset from edge for adding fillers
                           # (float, optional)
-ignoreSiteType            # don't check site type (bool, optional)
-ioRow <rowName>           # name of IO row to be processed (string, optional)
-logic                     # add fillers to net list in top module
                           # (bool, optional)
-powerDomain <string>      # add filler to power domain associated io rows
                           # (string, optional)
-prefix <string>           # prefix for new filler instances (string, optional)
-to <coord>                # ending offset from edge for adding fillers
                           # (float, optional)
-useSmallIoHeight          # match site before adding filler (bool, optional)